The paper deals with secure transmission strategies for multi-cell multi-user massive MIMO systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), multimedia (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY). The focus on eavesdropping and pilot contamination also suggests a strong connection to the security and privacy subfield of computer science.
